<body>
  <h1>Security Policy</h1>
  <small>Last updated: January 2025</small>
  <hr />

  <p>
    Gifted Hands Innovation is committed to maintaining a safe and secure browsing experience for our users.
    Our site is a static website hosted on GitHub Pages and does not process sensitive user data.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Supported Versions</h2>
  <p>
    Because this is a continuously updated static site, only the latest live version of the site
    is considered supported.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Reporting a Vulnerability</h2>
  <p>
    If you believe you have discovered a security issue affecting this website, we encourage you
    to report it responsibly.
  </p>
  <p>Please include:</p>
  <p>
    • A clear description of the issue<br/>
    • Steps to reproduce the behavior<br/>
    • Any screenshots or proof of concept if available
  </p>
  <p>
    Reports can be sent to:<br/>
    <strong>giftedhandsinnovation@gmail.com</strong>
  </p>
  <p>We aim to acknowledge valid reports within 72 hours.</p>

  <h2>3. Scope</h2>
  <p>In-scope items include:</p>
  <p>
    • HTML, CSS, and JavaScript served by this GitHub Pages site<br/>
    • Misconfigurations that could affect visitors<br/>
    • Unsafe redirects or links controlled by this site
  </p>

  <p>Out-of-scope items include:</p>
  <p>
    • Issues on Amazon or other third-party websites<br/>
    • Browser extensions, local device infections, or ISP-related problems<br/>
    • Denial-of-service attacks or spam tests
  </p>

  <h2>4. Responsible Disclosure</h2>
  <p>
    We request that you do not publicly disclose potential vulnerabilities before we have had a chance
    to review and address them. Responsible, private reporting helps keep everyone safe.
  </p>

  <p><a href="index.html">← Back to Home</a></p>
</body>
</html>
